net.enilink.komma.core

Interface IEntityManager

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IEntityManagerInternal
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractEntityManager, CachingEntityManager, DecoratingEntityManager, DelegatingEntityManager, EagerCachingEntityManager, ThreadLocalEntityManager

    public interface IEntityManager
extends AutoCloseable
    Interface used to interact with the underlying RDF store in terms of beans (entities).

    An IEntityManager instance is configured by a KommaModule that defines the concepts and behaviours used to map the entities. Each entity managed by an IEntityManager implements the interface IEntity that allows access to the associated entity manager.

    Entities are identified by an IReference that represents either a URI or a BlankNode. Instances of beans and corresponding references are equal in terms of the hashCode and equals methods.

    Instances of IEntityManager can be obtained through an IEntityManagerFactory that either creates user-managed instances via IEntityManagerFactory.create() or provides instances managed by an IUnitOfWork via IEntityManagerFactory.get().

      • remove

        void remove(Object entity)
        Removes the given entity or subject and all implementing roles. It is the responsibility of the caller to ensure this entity or any other object referencing it are no longer used and any object that may have cached a value containing this is refreshed.
        Parameters:
        entity - to be removed from the pool and repository.

      • rename

        <T> T rename(T entity,
             URI uri)
        Removes all the references to the given entity and replaces them with references to the new qname. It is the responsibility of the caller to ensure that any object references to this resource are replaced with the returned object. Previous referenced objects must no longer be used and any cached values must be refreshed.
        Parameters:
        entity - current Entity to be renamed
        uri - new qualified name of the entity
        Returns:
        entity with the given qname.
